    "narrative": "The heart of the LawDog lineup today is undeniably **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite score of 81.53 against Civale. With a favorable park factor and a solid SP skill adjustment, he is our clear engine for counting stats. Joining him as high-ceiling options are **Taylor Ward** (64.19) and **Bryson Stott** (63.48). Despite facing tough left-handed starters, **Taylor Ward** benefits from a massive +10% boost for leading off, while **Bryson Stott** draws a targetable matchup against Paddack, leveraging a strong +13% platoon edge that outweighs his bottom-third spot in the order. **Geraldo Perdomo** also earns a strong recommendation (61.37) by securing a leadoff-adjacent spot against Boyd; his ability to capitalize on wind-out conditions and favorable platoon positioning makes him a critical component of our stolen base strategy today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of the active roster at 43.18. While **Matt Chapman** projects as a reasonable start, he was pushed out by the higher efficiency and specific matchup advantages held by our active infielders. Meanwhile, we are exercising caution with **Masyn Winn** (47.61) and **Wenceel Perez** (48.07). While **Masyn Winn** receives a slight bump due to the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery\u2014enhancing his already elite sprint speed upside\u2014he remains a marginal play against a quality arm like Wrobleski. **Wenceel Perez** faces a similar situation; despite his 94% stolen base profile, the significant negative platoon adjustment against Leiter necessitates a measured approach. We are keeping **Yainer Diaz** and **Cal Raleigh** on the bench due to status uncertainty, but they remain priority targets to rotate into the utility slot once their confirmed presence in the lineup is verified.",
